\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. P. grandiflora} (L.) Scholler,{\i  Fl. Barb. }140 (1775). Sparsely pubescent; stems up to 60 cm. Leaves 5-9 × 3·5-4 cm, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, entire or crenulate; petiole (0-)4(-9) cm. Inflorescence not subtended by leaves. Bracts 15-20 × 15-20 mm. Calyx 15 mm, the teeth awned; teeth of upper lip subequal; teeth of lower lip 3-4 mm, broadly lanceolate, shortly ciliate. Corolla (18-)25-30 mm, the lips deep violet, the tube whitish. 2n = 28.{\i  Europe except for most of the north and the islands.} Al Au Be Bu Cz Da Ga Ge Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Lu Po Rm Rs (B, C, W, K, E) Su Tu.
