\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. P. hyssopifolia} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 600 (1753). Glabrous or sparsely pubescent; stems up to 40 cm. Leaves (1-)3-6(-8) × (0·3-)0·5-1·3(-1·8) cm, linear-lanceolate to elliptic-lanceolate, entire, sessile, rarely the lowest pair shortly petiolate. Inflorescence subtended by leaves. Bracts 10-12 × 10-13 mm. Calyx 8-9 mm, the teeth mucronate or awned; teeth of upper lip subequal; teeth of lower lip 3-3·5 mm, lanceolate, ciliate. Corolla 15-17 mm, violet, rarely whitish. •{\i  S.W. Europe. }Co Ga Hs It.
