\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 23.             Melissa }                 L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By R. Fernandes.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs. Verticillasters few- to many-flowered. Calyx campanulate, 2-lipped, 13-veined; upper lip flattened, 3-toothed lower lip 2-toothed. Corolla 2-lipped, the tube curved and dilated above the middle, without a ring of hairs inside; upper lip erect or deflexed, sometimes slightly hooded, emarginate lower lip 3-lobed. Stamens didynamous, included, convergent anther-cells divergent. Style-branches subequal.
\par

